tags: basically this is just a post about how killing eve gets everything right that ive been dissatisfied with in media for AGES.
summary: honestly another reason i think i’ve gotten so picky about dark, twisty ships is that the thing i really need to be present. in...
body:
honestly another reason i think i’ve gotten so picky about dark, twisty ships is that the thing i really need to be present. in order to connect with a ship. is that on some level these people, even if their relationship is catastrophic and complicated, need to get along and like… enjoy each other.

like for a super easy example, that’s why (or part of why) i always hated bangel when i was into btvs. they never seemed to do anything but make each other miserable. and it’s like, why do these people like… spend time with each other??

on some level that always got in the way of hannigram for me too, like i know that will and hannibal enjoy each other in a sense, but they were never like, the kind of people i could picture just doing something casual together. it’s like they’re solely attracted to each other’s darkness.

it just occurred to me that that’s a way to articulate that nuance i keep trying to find words for with villaneve: they are attracted to each other’s darkness, but also kind of… each other’s light? eve is almost constantly looking for reasons to humanize villanelle (though not like, unrealistic ones, she calls villanelle’s Fake Sympathy Ploy out pretty quickly) and wants to know all these stupid, normal things about her while villanelle seems like… at times more interested in just sitting in the same room as eve and getting to know her and making her laugh than ~manipulating her into darkness~ or whatever

essentially i just like. buy them as people who genuinely like each other, i guess, even though their relationship is also oftentimes ridiculously volatile and screwed up

summary: Watching the Detectives, a Discord server
title: Watching the Detectives, a Discord server
body:
Permanent link: Join server

A brand-new server for chatting about mystery/detective fandoms! Because I love detective fiction, and so do a lot of y’all. ;)

Like…Brooklyn 99…Killing Eve…Grantchester…Miss Fisher’s Murder Mysteries…Poirot…Peter Wimsey…The Ankh-Morpork City Watch…Juno Steel…Rivers of London…TAZ Amnesty…Hannibal…Pushing Daisies…Rusty Lake…Sherlock Holmes…Twin Peaks…and more!

Enticement(?): Chill queer founder/mod (me!) with lots of recs and Concepts, loves offbeat and marginalized protagonists, gets really into the clothes and food in between trying to predict the murderer.
